    "csaf_version": "2.0",
    "notes": [
      {
        "category": "summary",
        "text": "An update is available for corosync.\nThis update affects Rocky Linux 8.\nA Common Vulnerability Scoring System (CVSS) base score, which gives a detailed severity rating, is available for each vulnerability from the CVE list",
        "title": "Topic"
      },
      {
        "category": "description",
        "text": "The corosync packages provide the Corosync Cluster Engine and C APIs for Rocky Linux cluster software.\n\nSecurity Fix(es):\n\n* corosync: Corosync: Denial of Service and information disclosure via crafted UDP packet (CVE-2026-35091)\n\n* corosync: Corosync: Denial of Service via integer overflow in join message validation (CVE-2026-35092)\n\nFor more details about the security issue(s), including the impact, a CVSS score, acknowledgments, and other related information, refer to the CVE page(s) listed in the References section.\n\nThis advisory is provided by Ctrl IQ, Inc for Rocky Linux systems. For more information about CIQ security practices, visit https://ciq.com/security.",
        "title": "Description"
      }
    ],
